args: Our work here is done—which is good,\nbecause it's pretty late.
Let's hurry home and... Huh?\nWhat's going on there?
Oy there, little lady! Things like you\nshouldn't be wanderin' about at night.
She ain't listenin' to us. Still, someone's\ngonna miss her—and pay 'andsomely\nfor her safe return!
Don't worry, miss—we'll take ya 'ome.\nBwaaa ha ha ha!
Oh, just some heavily armed passer-by.\nLooks like this woman doesn't want\nto go with you.
The 'ell do we care what she wants?!

You two clearly aren't the sharpest tools
in the shed, so lemme lay this out for
you real clear: Let her go, or I'm going
to turn both of you into mincemeat.
Listen, you can't just be wandering around\nat night with your noggin in the clouds.
I know. I just wanted to take in some\nnight air and clear my head a little.
Listen, if you want to talk, I'm a pretty\ngood listener. What do you say?
Well, I had a fight with an old friend,\nand now we aren't speaking anymore.
And the more I think about it, the more I\nrealize how stupid the whole thing was.
Then go find them and apologize!
I think it's too late for that...
He's setting out for a long journey at sea,\nyou see, and he leaves at dawn.
So he's in port? Yeah, that's quite a ways\nfrom here.
Even if I start after him now, the ship\nwill be gone by the time I arrive.
That's not true. You can write him a letter!
You may not be able to make it to port,\nbut I'm fast. REALLY fast. If I run all night,\nI can get there just before his ship leaves.
But...I couldn't ask you to do that.
I WANT to do it. That's why I brought it up.
I'll go with you, Botan. An extra sword\nwill help on these dangerous roads.
Right then! Put out your pinky.
Because we're making a pinky promise.\nThat makes it totally unbreakable!
On my pinky, I swear to deliver your letter.
*pant pant* ...Man, running all night\nsure takes it out of a girl.
But I can't rest! I have to deliver\nthis letter before dawn!
We should be at the port once we pass\nthrough this... Wha?!
There are too many for us to fight.
But we don't have time to find\na different route!
Then I'll distract them while you slip past.
I'll fend them off for a bit and then run.\nWe'll meet up later at the port.
Aw, crumbles! There's still one here!\nAnd boy, does it look strong.
Sorry, fiend, but I gotta bolt.\nI have someone's message to deliver!
And if you won't step aside,\nI'll just go THROUGH you!
*pant* Oof. It took a lot longer than I\nthought to shake those fiends.
Where's Botan? She should have\narrived here before me.
Botan! Thank goodness you're all right.\nBut what about the letter?
You still have it? So you didn't make it...
Huh? Oh no, I delivered that one just fine!\nThis is his response.
He told me to give this to her along\nwith a super heartfelt apology.
Well, I'm glad they're able to make up.
Yeah, me too. It'd be sad to think of two\npeople spending the rest of their lives\nin some misunderstanding.
Right then! Time to hit the road.\nI've got a letter to deliver.
Don't you want to rest first?
Besides, I only know one speed:\nFULL-ON CRAZY! Wooooo!
